<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,973,999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Redescription.</emphasis>
Habitus typical of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Strenzke, K." box="[721,889,973,1000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" pagination="46 - 65" refId="ref5224" refString="Strenzke, K. (1954) Verbreitung und Systematik der Collembolen der deutschen Nord- und Ostseekuste. Veroffentlichungen des Instituts fur Meeresforschung in Bremerhaven, 3, 46 - 65." type="journal article" year="1954">Strenzke 1954</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[902,969,973,999]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity box="[1144,1298,973,1000]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.25" metricValueMax="8.5" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="0.725" valueMax="0.85" valueMin="0.6">0.6–0.85 mm</quantity>
. Color mottled grey-violet to gray-black. Ventrally paler. Borders between abdominal segments pale. Tegumental granulation coarse and uniform, 5–6 granules between setae p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[709,717,1064,1078]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">1</subScript>
on Abd. V (
<figureCitation box="[852,917,1045,1071]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
Body setae short (slightly longer on last abdominal segments), fine and smooth. Body sensilla (s) about two times longer than microsetae, fine and smooth. Chaetotaxy of head typical of the genus, with complete set of v-setae. Th. I with 3 + 3 setae. Dorsal chaetotaxy of Th. II and Abd. III–VI as in 
<figureCitation box="[1012,1112,1153,1179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Figs 1–4</figureCitation>
. Th. II with setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1336,1344,1172,1186]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">2</subScript>
, m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1380,1388,1172,1186]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">3</subScript>
and m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[173,181,1208,1222]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">4</subScript>
present. Th. III with setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[493,501,1208,1222]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">2</subScript>
and m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[575,583,1208,1222]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">3</subScript>
absent and setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[795,803,1208,1222]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">4</subScript>
present. Setae a 
<subScript attach="left" box="[981,989,1208,1222]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">6</subScript>
on Th. II–III sometimes absent.Abd. IV with setae p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[283,291,1244,1258]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">3</subScript>
and p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[357,365,1244,1258]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">7</subScript>
present. Abd. V with setae p 
<subScript attach="left" box="[679,687,1244,1258]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">2</subScript>
present, setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[870,878,1244,1258]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">1</subScript>
usually absent (only 
<specimenCount box="[1114,1266,1225,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1332,1436,1225,1251]" name="Denmark" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Denmark</collectingCountry>
with unpaired setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[400,408,1280,1294]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">1</subScript>
present) and setae m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[648,656,1280,1294]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">3</subScript>
quite often present (usually unpairly). Subcoxae I, II, III with 1, 2, 3 setae, respectively. Microsensillum on Th. II present (
<figureCitation box="[753,822,1297,1323]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
Ant. IV with simple apical vesicle, subapical organite (or), microsensillum (ms), 6–8 weakly differentiated cylindrical, curved sensilla (3 lateral and 3–5 dorsal) (
<figureCitation box="[762,829,1369,1396]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) and 5–7 short pointed setae in ventral field. Ant. IIIorgan with two long (outer) and two short (inner) sensilla. Microsensillum on Ant. III present (
<figureCitation box="[1223,1292,1405,1432]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Ant. I with 7 setae (seta p’ absent).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
Ocelli: 8 + 8. Postantennal organ 1.2–2.0 as long as neighbouring ocelli, with four lobes, the anterior pair slightly larger than posterior one. Accessory boss most often invisible (
<figureCitation box="[938,1003,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Strenzke, K." box="[1056,1220,1513,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" pagination="46 - 65" refId="ref5224" refString="Strenzke, K. (1954) Verbreitung und Systematik der Collembolen der deutschen Nord- und Ostseekuste. Veroffentlichungen des Instituts fur Meeresforschung in Bremerhaven, 3, 46 - 65." type="journal article" year="1954">Strenzke 1954</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1230,1328,1513,1539]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
). Labrum without apical papillae. Labral setae 5, 5, 4, prelabrals 4. Maxillary head as in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A." box="[1038,1216,1549,1575]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" refId="ref4537" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1998) The Collembola of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Part 1 Poduromorpha. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica. Brill, Leiden, Boston and Koln, 184 pp." type="book" year="1998">Fjellberg (1998</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1227,1323,1549,1576]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 11d</figureCitation>
). Lamella 1 broadened at tip, protruding beyond teeth, with two fringes of long cilia. Labial palp as shown in 
<bibRefCitation author="Fjellberg, A." box="[1256,1433,1585,1611]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" pagination="309 - 330" refId="ref4570" refString="Fjellberg, A. (1999) The labial palp in Collembola. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 237, 309 - 330." type="journal article" year="1999">Fjellberg (1999</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[151,219,1621,1648]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Outer maxillary lobe with two sublobal hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
Tibiotarsi I, II, III with 19, 19, 18 setae, respectively. Apical seta A1 weakly clavate, slightly longer than inner edge of claw. Claws without inner tooth. Empodial appendage lancet-like, basal lamella absent. Ratio empodial appendage/inner edge of claws = 0.25–0.4 (
<figureCitation box="[614,680,1729,1756]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Strenzke, K." box="[735,900,1729,1756]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" pagination="46 - 65" refId="ref5224" refString="Strenzke, K. (1954) Verbreitung und Systematik der Collembolen der deutschen Nord- und Ostseekuste. Veroffentlichungen des Instituts fur Meeresforschung in Bremerhaven, 3, 46 - 65." type="journal article" year="1954">Strenzke 1954</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[910,1010,1729,1756]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" box="[199,1002,1765,1792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Ventral tube with four setae on each side. Retinaculum with 3 + 3 teeth.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
Furca well developed (ratio dens + mucro/inner edge of claw III = 2.7–3.2). Dorsal side of dens with 7 setae and with coarse, uniform granulation. Ratio dens/mucro = 3–4. Mucro slightly curved, with globular tip and high outer lamella ending just before the apex (
<figureCitation box="[559,671,1873,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Figs 8–11</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Strenzke, K." box="[725,890,1873,1900]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" pagination="46 - 65" refId="ref5224" refString="Strenzke, K. (1954) Verbreitung und Systematik der Collembolen der deutschen Nord- und Ostseekuste. Veroffentlichungen des Instituts fur Meeresforschung in Bremerhaven, 3, 46 - 65." type="journal article" year="1954">Strenzke 1954</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[901,1009,1873,1900]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[158,1425,187,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1279]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–11. H. gisini: 5, chaetotaxy of Ant. III–IV; 6, postantennal organ and ocelli; 7, claw III with empodial appendage; 8, dens and mucro; 9, mucro, lateral view; 10, mucro, lateral view (variant); 11, mucro, lateral view (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669056" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669056/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 7a–c</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,757,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">
Anal spines short (ratio anal spines/inner edge of claws III = 0.3–0.5), slightly curved, on separate papillae of same length as spines (
<figureCitation box="[408,475,1945,1971]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Strenzke, K." box="[529,694,1945,1972]" pageId="1" pageNumber="53" pagination="46 - 65" refId="ref5224" refString="Strenzke, K. (1954) Verbreitung und Systematik der Collembolen der deutschen Nord- und Ostseekuste. Veroffentlichungen des Instituts fur Meeresforschung in Bremerhaven, 3, 46 - 65." type="journal article" year="1954">Strenzke 1954</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[705,773,1945,1971]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1365,189,1904]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[198,1389,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. H. gisini: 1, tegumental granulation of Abd. V; 2, chaetotaxy of Th. II; 3, chaetotaxy of Abd. III–VI; 4, chaetotaxy of Abd. V (variant). Abbreviations in text. Scale bar 0.01 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6669054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6669054/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="53">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
